# .gitignore
# This file tells Git which things to NEVER upload to GitHub.
# Anything listed here stays only on your own computer.

# --- Secrets (most important) ---
# Later you'll keep passwords, email logins, and payment keys in a
# file like this. It must never go to GitHub.
.env
*.key
secrets.py

# --- Your database ---
# When you add the database in step 2, it creates a file like this.
# It holds your real data and shouldn't be uploaded.
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# --- Uploaded books ---
# The actual PDF files your admin panel will accept don't belong
# in your code repo (they can be large and aren't code).
uploads/
*.pdf

# --- Python clutter ---
# Python auto-generates these; nobody needs them on GitHub.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
venv/
.venv/
